1
00:00:50,820 --> 00:00:52,400
Hey, how are you doing today?

2
00:00:53,745 --> 00:00:55,289
How many eggs did you lay?

3
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:09,060
Whoa.

4
00:01:09,155 --> 00:01:09,837
Hey...

5
00:01:10,394 --> 00:01:11,940
They really lay eggs every day?

6
00:01:13,053 --> 00:01:14,812
If it feels comfortable, then yeah, every day.

7
00:01:16,447 --> 00:01:17,117
So that means

8
00:01:17,390 --> 00:01:20,042
maybe we shouldn’t get too close to it.

9
00:01:20,156 --> 00:01:23,028
If it gets stressed, it might stop laying eggs.

10
00:01:24,295 --> 00:01:26,806
I doubt it’d get stressed around someone like you.

11
00:01:28,136 --> 00:01:28,757
Why’s that?

12
00:01:29,612 --> 00:01:32,334
Because it probably thinks you’re one of them.

13
00:01:32,783 --> 00:01:34,365
Always staying inside your own cage.

14
00:01:36,828 --> 00:01:39,320
So this is what you meant when you said

15
00:01:39,910 --> 00:01:41,840
you’re gentle with all your guests?

16
00:01:42,898 --> 00:01:43,933
I am gentle.

17
00:01:44,856 --> 00:01:45,728
It’s just that some people

18
00:01:45,864 --> 00:01:48,358
love challenging my feelings.

19
00:01:55,196 --> 00:01:58,945
Did this chicken hate me in a past life or something?

20
00:02:01,366 --> 00:02:02,327
Well, you

21
00:02:02,666 --> 00:02:04,275
walked in without permission.

22
00:02:05,789 --> 00:02:06,497
Hey...

23
00:02:06,849 --> 00:02:10,281
They are chickens, not people.

24
00:02:11,011 --> 00:02:12,910
And what about you?

25
00:02:13,437 --> 00:02:16,957
Have you ever asked permission before writing about people’s feelings like that?

26
00:02:17,432 --> 00:02:19,052
Or is that the only way

27
00:02:19,245 --> 00:02:21,878
to escape from your own feelings?

28
00:02:27,453 --> 00:02:30,124
Maybe you should start by not trying to explain everything

29
00:02:30,365 --> 00:02:31,782
like the way you are doing.

30
00:02:33,419 --> 00:02:34,114
And...

31
00:02:35,919 --> 00:02:37,180
what if I can’t stop?

32
00:02:38,637 --> 00:02:39,137
Because...

33
00:02:39,455 --> 00:02:41,113
if I don't have a reason.

34
00:02:41,929 --> 00:02:43,929
I’ll just get even more scared.

35
00:02:44,815 --> 00:02:46,156
Then maybe you should let yourself be scared for once.

36
00:02:46,682 --> 00:02:48,682
So you’ll know what real feelings are like.

37
00:03:33,227 --> 00:03:35,898
Even with a view this beautiful right in front of you

38
00:03:36,595 --> 00:03:39,900
you’re still staring at your keyboard?

39
00:03:41,338 --> 00:03:41,838
Well...

40
00:03:42,556 --> 00:03:44,151
it isn't going anywhere...

41
00:03:44,799 --> 00:03:47,547
but the ideas in my head is.

42
00:03:50,407 --> 00:03:51,330
Then...

43
00:03:52,402 --> 00:03:54,040
when you write,

44
00:03:54,860 --> 00:03:56,860
what voice do you hear in your head?

45
00:04:00,001 --> 00:04:00,501
Probably...

46
00:04:01,123 --> 00:04:03,909
my own thoughts, I guess.

47
00:04:05,096 --> 00:04:06,060
The voice that...

48
00:04:08,393 --> 00:04:10,393
keeps trying to make sense of everything.

49
00:04:12,166 --> 00:04:13,216
And...

50
00:04:13,959 --> 00:04:16,580
does that voice ever go quiet?

51
00:04:17,753 --> 00:04:18,977
Hardly ever.

52
00:04:19,877 --> 00:04:20,641
Except...

53
00:04:21,441 --> 00:04:23,124
when someone’s voice

54
00:04:23,339 --> 00:04:25,934
is the one I want to hear instead.

55
00:04:51,122 --> 00:04:52,197
Staring at me like that...

56
00:04:52,498 --> 00:04:54,000
is there something you want me to prove?

57
00:04:55,062 --> 00:04:55,770
No.

58
00:04:56,670 --> 00:04:59,392
When you’re focused on something

59
00:04:59,802 --> 00:05:01,270
you feel different from

60
00:05:01,761 --> 00:05:03,860
when we’re arguing.

61
00:05:05,772 --> 00:05:06,360
Then...

62
00:05:06,921 --> 00:05:09,200
maybe I should stop talking for a while.

63
00:05:09,909 --> 00:05:12,707
Then I’ll hear my heart more clearly.

64
00:05:21,114 --> 00:05:25,433
Silence between two people doesn’t always mean there’s nothing to say.

65
00:05:26,162 --> 00:05:27,478
Sometimes...

66
00:05:27,866 --> 00:05:31,462
it’s the moment when your heart finally hears itself again.

67
00:05:31,750 --> 00:05:33,060
I had no idea

68
00:05:33,533 --> 00:05:35,128
what she was thinking.

69
00:05:35,790 --> 00:05:37,321
But in that silence...

70
00:05:37,668 --> 00:05:40,276
I could hear my own heart more clearly than ever.

71
00:06:00,742 --> 00:06:02,413
This kind of atmosphere...

72
00:06:02,735 --> 00:06:04,456
is perfect for writing.

73
00:06:08,091 --> 00:06:09,000
Looks like...

74
00:06:09,229 --> 00:06:10,469
it's raining.

75
00:06:12,856 --> 00:06:13,807
Hey, wait!

76
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:17,740
Ow!

77
00:06:17,740 --> 00:06:20,551
You can’t just run past people like that. What if you hit someone?

78
00:06:20,866 --> 00:06:22,848
It’s because my papers are...

79
00:06:28,830 --> 00:06:29,330
Hey!

80
00:06:29,824 --> 00:06:31,153
What are you doing?

81
00:06:46,395 --> 00:06:48,395
You really didn’t have to go that far.

82
00:06:48,495 --> 00:06:49,519
It’s just paper.

83
00:06:50,205 --> 00:06:52,205
But sometimes the things that you look past

84
00:06:52,465 --> 00:06:55,263
might be the reason someone still wants to stay.

85
00:06:57,967 --> 00:06:58,972
Thank you.

86
00:07:00,981 --> 00:07:03,305
I just didn’t want the next book to end

87
00:07:03,305 --> 00:07:05,305
before it even began.

88
00:07:12,129 --> 00:07:16,308
Sometimes your heart doesn’t race because of sweet words.

89
00:07:16,769 --> 00:07:18,478
It races because

90
00:07:18,864 --> 00:07:20,864
of the sincerity.

91
00:07:21,524 --> 00:07:23,524
And honestly...

92
00:07:23,851 --> 00:07:25,040
I don’t even know when

93
00:07:25,289 --> 00:07:27,289
my heart started reacting to little things like this.

94
00:07:59,224 --> 00:08:02,240
She’s usually sitting here typing every morning.

95
00:08:10,012 --> 00:08:12,012
She always do the same things...

96
00:08:12,012 --> 00:08:13,138
When she disappeared like this,

97
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:17,367
it made me worry.

98
00:08:20,433 --> 00:08:21,560
Without her...

99
00:08:22,118 --> 00:08:23,903
I should be able to write more, right?

100
00:08:25,691 --> 00:08:27,691
So why does everything feel so quiet?

101
00:08:28,867 --> 00:08:30,000
That’s weird.

102
00:08:30,882 --> 00:08:32,535
It’s only been one morning.

103
00:08:43,482 --> 00:08:45,482
This isn’t my equation at all.

104
00:09:02,886 --> 00:09:03,386
Hey...

105
00:09:04,478 --> 00:09:07,226
reading someone else’s journal is against the rules, you know.

106
00:09:08,220 --> 00:09:10,220
I wasn’t trying to read it.

107
00:09:10,304 --> 00:09:11,715
I was just afraid it’d blow away again.

108
00:09:13,389 --> 00:09:14,071
That’s good.

109
00:09:14,722 --> 00:09:15,658
Because in there

110
00:09:16,022 --> 00:09:18,022
there are more secrets than you think.

111
00:09:19,728 --> 00:09:21,551
A writer’s secrets?

112
00:09:22,065 --> 00:09:26,168
Are you hiding your feelings there?

113
00:09:27,560 --> 00:09:29,068
You always know exactly what to say.

114
00:09:46,969 --> 00:09:49,615
I tried keeping my distance to prove it was nothing.

115
00:09:50,105 --> 00:09:50,605
But

116
00:09:50,690 --> 00:09:52,513
it became too quiet.

117
00:09:53,006 --> 00:09:55,348
Quiet enough to hear my heartbeat louder than the keyboard.

118
00:09:55,601 --> 00:09:57,069
I don’t know where she went

119
00:09:57,447 --> 00:09:58,960
but the thing that disappeared

120
00:09:59,161 --> 00:10:01,060
made everything around me louder.

121
00:10:01,807 --> 00:10:05,049
Including the feelings I kept trying

122
00:10:05,252 --> 00:10:06,400
not to admit.

